<h2 id="who-its-for">👤 Who Each Platform Is For</h2>

**Choose Vagaro if:**
- You're a solo provider or small team (1-5 providers)
- Budget constraints make every dollar matter
- Your service menu is straightforward without complex packages
- You want integrated payroll without additional vendors
- Marketplace visibility provides meaningful value
- You're operating 1-3 locations with standardized operations

**Choose Boulevard if:**
- You're running a premium brand where client experience differentiates
- Membership revenue exceeds 30% of total revenue
- You need sophisticated reporting for investor or franchise requirements
- Multi-location operations demand centralized management
- Your commission structure requires platform flexibility
- You have technical resources to maximize API integrations

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> If you're currently on Vagaro and frustrated with limitations, don't switch to Boulevard immediately. First, maximize Vagaro's capabilities with their advanced features. Our team frequently finds operators using 40% of available Vagaro functionality before considering migration.
</div>

For med spa operators specifically, the HIPAA compliance question matters. Both platforms offer [HIPAA-compliant configurations](/guides/hipaa-compliance-spa-software), but Boulevard's forms and consent management integrates more seamlessly with clinical workflows. Vagaro requires more careful configuration to maintain compliance at scale.

<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

The Vagaro vs Boulevard decision ultimately reflects your operational maturity and growth trajectory more than feature checklists.

**Vagaro wins on value.** For the vast majority of spa and salon operators—particularly those under $500,000 annual revenue or fewer than 6 providers—Vagaro delivers comprehensive functionality at pricing that makes business sense. The marketplace provides client acquisition that Boulevard users pay separately to replicate. The integrated payroll eliminates vendor complexity.

**Boulevard wins on sophistication.** Premium brands, med spa groups, and multi-location operators with complex membership models need Boulevard's infrastructure. The client experience differentiation matters when you're charging $300 for facials instead of $90. The reporting depth supports data-driven operations that Vagaro can't match.

Our recommendation for operators evaluating both: start with Vagaro unless you have specific, documented requirements that only Boulevard addresses. You can always migrate up as your operation matures. Migrating down rarely happens without frustration.

For med spa operators specifically considering [alternatives to both platforms](/comparisons/medspa-software-comparison), evaluate whether spa-specific platforms like Aesthetic Record or specialized EHR-first systems better address clinical requirements.

